0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-view","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-header","style":{"background":"#dbeafe"},"children":["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-header-inner","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"back-btn","children":"← Back to Blog"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"blog-tag","style":{"marginBottom":"1rem","display":"inline-block"},"children":"Tech & Accessories"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"blog-post-title","children":"Best USB-C Hubs for a Clean Desk Setup (2026)"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":"May 29, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"8 min read"}]]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"blog-post-body","children":[["$","p","p-0",{"children":"A laptop with two USB-C ports and nothing else is a productivity bottleneck. A bad USB-C hub makes it worse — dropped connections, slow charging pass-through, or a hub that runs hot enough to throttle everything connected to it."}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":"After testing eight hubs over six weeks with a MacBook Pro and a Windows laptop, here's what actually works."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"What to Look for in a USB-C Hub"}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Port selection."}]," Most people need: HDMI (4K@60Hz minimum), two USB-A ports, one USB-C data port, SD card reader, and 100W power delivery pass-through. Anything less is a compromise."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Chipset quality."}]," Cheap hubs use low-quality chipsets that cause dropped connections, flickering displays, or heat buildup that throttles performance. This isn't something you can see in product photos."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Build temperature."}]," I measured each hub's surface temperature during a 2-hour work session. Anything above 45°C is a concern for longevity."]}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"The Tested Hubs"}],"\n",["$","table","table-0",{"children":[["$","thead","thead-0",{"children":["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","th","th-0",{"children":"Hub"}],["$","th","th-1",{"children":"Ports"}],["$","th","th-2",{"children":"PD"}],["$","th","th-3",{"children":"4K@60Hz"}],["$","th","th-4",{"children":"Avg Temp"}]]}]}],["$","tbody","tbody-0",{"children":[["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"Anker 555 (7-in-1)"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"7"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"100W"}],["$","td","td-3",{"children":"Yes"}],["$","td","td-4",{"children":"38°C"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-1",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"Anker 332 (5-in-1)"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"5"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"85W"}],["$","td","td-3",{"children":"Yes"}],["$","td","td-4",{"children":"36°C"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-2",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"CalDigit TS4"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"18"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"98W"}],["$","td","td-3",{"children":"Yes"}],["$","td","td-4",{"children":"41°C"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-3",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"Satechi Slim (5-in-1)"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"5"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"60W"}],["$","td","td-3",{"children":"No (30Hz)"}],["$","td","td-4",{"children":"33°C"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-4",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"Amazon Basics 7-in-1"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"7"}],["$","td","td-2",{"children":"60W"}],["$","td","td-3",{"children":"No (30Hz)"}],["$","td","td-4",{"children":"44°C"}]]}]]}]]}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"The Winner: Anker 555 (7-in-1)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"children":"The Anker 555 consistently delivered 4K@60Hz with no dropped connections across both laptops. Power delivery held at 100W even under load. Surface temperature stayed well under 40°C during extended sessions."}],"\n",["$","p","p-6",{"children":"At ~$50 it's not the cheapest option, but it's the one I'd recommend without hesitation for most home office setups."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-3",{"children":"Best Budget Pick: Anker 332 (5-in-1)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-7",{"children":"If you only need one display output and can live without an SD card reader, the 332 does everything right at ~$30. Same reliable chipset as the 555, just fewer ports."}],"\n","$L3","\n","$L4","\n","$L5","\n","$L6"]}]]}],null,"$L7"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"WsuXEMkHw93YGaIBCBdDo"}
